      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Oh, sorry! I got a little too excited about the goblin situation and forgot to finish the sentence. The goblin in the kitchen is just a metaphor for that tiny, mischievous spirit that lives inside every pot of hollandaise, ready to throw a tantrum if the heat gets too high.\n\nTo answer your question about fixing it: If you whisk vigorously while adding a splash of warm water, you might be able to re-emulsify the butter back into the yolk. If that fails, you can try making a new batch using the leftover yolks and a fresh knob of butter, or even use the \"goblin trick\" of adding a little hot water to the curdled sauce to loosen it up before whisking again.\n\nSo, to recap: it happens because the heat stressed the proteins, but you can often fix it by cooling it down and adding a bit of liquid while whisking. If you're still stuck, just start over with fresh ingredients and keep an eye on the heat!",
